==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shamoying
<hw>Sha*moy"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Shammy</er>.]</ety> <def>A process used in preparing certain kinds
of leather, which consists in frizzing the skin, and working oil into it
to supply the place of the astringent (tannin, alum, or the like)
ordinarily used in tanning.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shampoo</ent>⟦br⟧
